dynamical phase\ntransition of the dissipative system in the limit of large system sizes. Our\nresults show that dynamical phase transitions are not restricted to occur in\nisolated systems, but, surprisingly, are possible also during the dissipative\nevolution of open quantum systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Aug 2022 05:59:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-11"}
