f the cluster is detected, spanning\n$\\sim$ 50$^\\circ$ long on sky. The signature matches with the mock stream's\ntrajectory well. Conclusions. Our results support that Triangulum stream acts\nas a part of the leading tail for NGC 5824. On the trailing side, we have\ndetected a 50$^\\circ$ tail extended from the cluster. The existence of both\nleading and trailing tails for the GC NGC 5824 is verified.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Aug 2022 07:35:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-09"}
